<span id="freeTextContainer17185644550245008117">I read in her biography (<a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/27058.James_Tiptree__Jr__The_Double_Life_of_Alice_B__Sheldon' title='James Tiptree, Jr. The Double Life of Alice B. Sheldon by Julie Phillips' rel='nofollow noopener'>James Tiptree, Jr.: The Double Life of Alice B. Sheldon</a>) she was uncomfortable with the novel format and they had to push her into it. That makes me feel better. I worship Tiptree, but it hurt to try to read this back in the day and it hurt again last year. She was a short story writer. Though she seems to settle at the extended short story of a hundred pages. </span>
  <span id="freeText17185644550245008117" style="display:none">I read in her biography (<a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/27058.James_Tiptree__Jr__The_Double_Life_of_Alice_B__Sheldon" title="James Tiptree, Jr. The Double Life of Alice B. Sheldon by Julie Phillips" rel="nofollow noopener">James Tiptree, Jr.: The Double Life of Alice B. Sheldon</a>) she was uncomfortable with the novel format and they had to push her into it. That makes me feel better. I worship Tiptree, but it hurt to try to read this back in the day and it hurt again last year. She was a short story writer. Though she seems to settle at the extended short story of a hundred pages. </span>
