<span id="freeTextContainer1807237966947531050">A very beautiful book that touches on so many things - colonialism, capitalism, exploitation, genocide, sex work, cultural conflict, greed, love, death, illness, memory. The prose is lyrical, the characters are compelling, the story is heartfelt and gut-wrenchingly ugly. Three members of the Galactic military are stationed on an outpost at the far end of the galaxy. They are tasked with guarding the native inhabitants who have been brutally ravished by other humans and also giving tours to peopl</span>
  <span id="freeText1807237966947531050" style="display:none">A very beautiful book that touches on so many things - colonialism, capitalism, exploitation, genocide, sex work, cultural conflict, greed, love, death, illness, memory. The prose is lyrical, the characters are compelling, the story is heartfelt and gut-wrenchingly ugly. Three members of the Galactic military are stationed on an outpost at the far end of the galaxy. They are tasked with guarding the native inhabitants who have been brutally ravished by other humans and also giving tours to people who want to visit. When the story starts, a new group of visitors arrive, some expected, some not, and some may have ulterior motives. Meanwhile they are expecting the last remnants of a supernova to pass over the planet. Can the three track the waves of the supernova (which was triggered during a war) and keep an eye on the visitors? Read and find out. It's worth your time.</span>
