<span id="freeTextContainer10877457895277050958">This is the first Tiptree book/story I read and I apparently made a mistake to start here. While she does some decent world building and the concept is interesting enough the story is slow paced as all hell and the characters aren’t all that compelling. It’s written in a mystery book style as well which I’m personally not generally a fan of. I think the only reason I got through it was because it was the only thing I had to read on a 9 hour international flight. I’ve heard great things about Tip</span>
  <span id="freeText10877457895277050958" style="display:none">This is the first Tiptree book/story I read and I apparently made a mistake to start here. While she does some decent world building and the concept is interesting enough the story is slow paced as all hell and the characters aren’t all that compelling. It’s written in a mystery book style as well which I’m personally not generally a fan of. I think the only reason I got through it was because it was the only thing I had to read on a 9 hour international flight. I’ve heard great things about Tiptree and other reviews have said this isn’t her best work so I’ll probably give her another chance and check out some of the short stories. As far as this one though, I can’t recommend it.</span>
