<div id="review_3533976447" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3533976447" />
    <a title="Mike" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/18846663-mike"><img alt="Mike" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1607618588p2/18846663.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3533976447?book_show_action=true">Sep 05, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mike" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mike" href="/user/show/18846663-mike">Mike</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3533976447" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17065897816235970746">I had found this in my library as a teenager and must have read it 5 times. I had no idea about the authors backstory untill after I had moved on. I finally decided to see if it holds up. The answer is... Pretty much, yes.<br/><br/>It reads like a 70s/80s sci fi novel, but I&apos;m not sure how to explain that further. The emotional scenes don&apos;t pack quite the punch I remember but it still hot me. The denouement was so long, which also seems uncommon today.<br/><br/>I&apos;m glad I reread it.</span>
  <span id="freeText17065897816235970746" style="display:none">I had found this in my library as a teenager and must have read it 5 times. I had no idea about the authors backstory untill after I had moved on. I finally decided to see if it holds up. The answer is... Pretty much, yes.<br /><br />It reads like a 70s/80s sci fi novel, but I'm not sure how to explain that further. The emotional scenes don't pack quite the punch I remember but it still hot me. The denouement was so long, which also seems uncommon today.<br /><br />I'm glad I reread it.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17065897816235970746" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


