<span id="freeTextContainer18018177020739738238">3.75* rounded up. Belatedly finishing this for the Women&apos;s ClassicSFF Readathon. My first Tiptree so I can&apos;t judge it vs the rest of her oeuvre but there were a lot of elements in this that come from the mystery/thriller genre so a part of me was charmed and swept along in it. the world building definitly has some disturbing elements in it but overall i found it quite a snappy read.</span>
  <span id="freeText18018177020739738238" style="display:none">3.75* rounded up. Belatedly finishing this for the Women's ClassicSFF Readathon. My first Tiptree so I can't judge it vs the rest of her oeuvre but there were a lot of elements in this that come from the mystery/thriller genre so a part of me was charmed and swept along in it. the world building definitly has some disturbing elements in it but overall i found it quite a snappy read.</span>
